                        <interp inst="t18400914-name-401" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES BARNES</persName>
                  </hi>. I am shopman to William Darby, an oilman, in Queen's-buildings, Brompton. The prisoner came on the 5th of Septem<lb></lb>ber for a quarter of a pound of soap and a quarter of a pound of soda—after she had paid for them, I observed her take a piece of soap from the box, and place it under her arm—she was walking out, I took hold of her and accused her of it—she denied it—I lifted her arm up, and it dropped from her.</p>
